1.title: Importance of Wetlands

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

1.plot: Terri and Todd explore wetlands though out North America and examine how important these areas are and take an in depth look at the creatures found there.

2.title: Wildlife of Puerto Rico

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

2.plot: Puerto Rico is rich with wild creatures and Terri, Todd, and Ashley go from one end of the island to the other examining this diverse ecosystem and the animals that call it home.

3.title: Creatures of the Night

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

3.plot: Nocturnal animals are the focus as Terri and Todd go out after dark to study their behaviors. They also come across these night creatures during the day, giving a unique perspective on what makes the animals they find so special.

4.title: Wings

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

4.plot: Every adventure Todd and Terri have taken has found them in the presence of birds, and today they not only check out what makes them special, but also what makes each different.

5.title: Hoofed Animals

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

5.plot: The hoofed animals of North America are some of the largest, fastest, and strongest on earth. Join Todd and Terri and they examine what makes each one so incredible.

6.title: The Beauty of Puerto Rico

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

6.plot: This beautiful island paradise offers something for everyone, from beaches to deserts, and jungles to plains. Today Terri, Todd, and Ashley travel to each of them to offer their unique perspective.

7.title: The Salty Seas

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

7.plot: The seas are home to creatures of all sizes, from snails to whales. And thriving in the salty waters can be challenging. Join Todd and Terri as they get up close to the creatures that make the oceans their home.

8.title: Reptilian Finds

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

8.plot: Todd has always found reptiles fascinating, and reluctantly, now Terri does too. On today's show they travel the western hemisphere seeking out their favorites, and show you what makes them so special.

9.title: Terri's Fantastic Finds

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

9.plot: Terri's adventurous spirit has taken her to so some incredible locations, and has found some amazing creatures. Follow her as she looks back at these areas, with Todd tagging along.

10.title: Todd's Tales

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

10.plot: The stories Todd can tell about the nature he has encountered is vast to say the least. On this episode he relives these stories in words and of course video, with Terri helping all the way.

11.title: The Waters of the Caribbean

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

11.plot: Terri and Todd travel to Puerto Rico, with Ashley, and go under the sea to get up close to the animals that make the Caribbean their home.

12.title: Beautiful Places

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

12.plot: Todd and Terri travel to some of the most beautiful landscapes in North America. From mountains to deserts, they take on a tour of these areas, some of which you may never have heard of before.

13.title: Creatures of the Prairie

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

13.plot: The vastness of the prairie is home to a number of fascinating animals. Terri and Todd get up close and personal with the creatures, some of which will surprise you.

1.title: Walking with Black Bears

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

1.plot: Experience what it would be like to walk among Black Bears in the wild, as Terri and Todd visit the Vince Shute Wildlife Sanctuary near Orr, MN, a magic circle in the heart of Minnesota's North Woods, where wildlife abounds!

2.title: The Little Wagon Train on the Prairie

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

2.plot: Ride along with Terri and Todd as they travel on an old fashioned Wagon Train across the South Dakota prairie. On the wagon train they get a taste of life as early settlers experienced it. They discover the wildlife and history that lies within the prairies and realize how brutal life on the prairie can be.

3.title: Creatures of the Sand Hills of Nebraska

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

3.plot: The Sandhills of Nebraska are a unique habitat which makes a perfect home to many unique creatures and various reptiles species. Come along with Todd and Terri as they explore the Sand Hills Region in search of various lizard species and Ornate Box Turtles, but end up finding so much more!

4.title: A Week in Northern Minnesota

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

4.plot: Terri and Todd attend the Minnesota Governors Fishing Opener at Lake Kabetogama where they visit with Governor Pawlenty about the Minnesota outdoors. They take in the sites and get a bird's eye view of the Canadian border. They encounter eagles, loons, deer, pelican, and find signs of moose nearby!

5.title: A Voyage to Isle Royale National Park

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

5.plot:

6.title: Behind the Scenes at Reptile Gardens

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

6.plot: Terri and Todd visit Reptile Gardens where they go behind the scenes and get hands-on with various reptiles, including alligators, crocodiles, a Timber Rattlesnake, and more! Terri and Todd quickly learn that working at Reptile Gardens is hard work, and not all glamorous!

7.title: The North Shore of Lake Superior

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

7.plot: Come along as Terri and Todd visit destinations on the North Shore of Lake Superior. They also take a cruise where they get to enjoy the sites, wildlife, and get a lesson on commercial fishing. Terri hops on board a small plane for a birds eye view of the area!

8.title: Custer State Park

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

8.plot: Terri and Todd explore Custer State Park in the Black Hills of South Dakota. On their journey, they see many hoofed animals such as Bison, Elk, Big Horn Sheep, and Pronghorn Antelope. They also discover a Yellow Bellied Marmot and a Bushy Tailed Wood Rat. See what happens when Todd gets too close to the bison!

9.title: A Nature Adventures Vacation to Ely Minnesota

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

9.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

10.title: The Best of the Black Hills

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

10.plot: Terri and Todd visit the Black Hills Region, where they explore the Deadwood area, Custer State Park and Roughlock Falls. They encounter many creatures including a Yellow Bellied Racer, Ruffed Grouse, Elk, Wild Turkeys, Big Horn Sheep, Antelope, Wandering Garter Snake, and a Sand Hill Crane!

11.title: Preserving Wildlife in Southeastern Minnesota

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

11.plot: Terri and Todd travel to the Wabasha, MN area in search of the Blanding's Turtle! They visit the Weaver Dunes Natural Area, the National Eagle Center, and take a tour of the backwaters of the Mississippi River where they find egrets, herons, eagles, Sand Hill Cranes, and Canada Geese!

12.title: Road Encounters of the Furry Kind

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

12.plot: Todd and Terri showcase some of the different creatures they have spotted along the road in their journeys, including Sandpipers, Mule Deer, Coyotes, and a skunk! Outside the car, they are dive-bombed by Common Nighthawks and find Great Horned Owl fledglings that are just learning to fly!

13.title: Unique Birds of the Prairie

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

13.plot: Todd and Terri explore the Great Plains in search of unique bird species such as Red Tailed Hawks and Long Billed Curlews. Not all birds live in nests, such as the Burrowing Owls they find near the Badlands. Terri finds a Pale Milk Snake, potential prey for birds.

1.title: Reptile Gardens: Friends Helping Friends

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

1.plot: Todd and Terri visit Herpetologist Terry Phillip at Reptile Gardens, seeking advice on reptiles. In exchange for Terry's help and advice, Terri agrees to return the favor by helping him out with a chore. You will cringe when you learn what chore they give her, and shocked when she actually does it!

2.title: Grand Lake, Co: Gateway to Rocky Mountain National Park

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

2.plot: Terri and Todd visit Grand Lake, Colorado. They encounter an array of wildlife, including Rocky Mountain Elk, American Pika, Yellow Bellied Marmots, Big Horn Sheep and Stellar Jays! They were mesmerized by the beauty, from forests and meadows, to alpine tundra and snow-covered peaks!

3.title: Mobridge SD: Gateway to the Western Prairie

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

3.plot: Terri and Todd visit the Mobridge, South Dakota area where they experience life and wildlife on the prairie. They try their hand at geocaching and showcase Swainson's Hawks, Short-Eared Owls and Bison! When leaving the area, they run in to a fierce, tornado-producing storm!

4.title: Terri and Todd: The Otter Spotters

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

4.plot: Terri and Todd travel to the Grand Rapids, Minnesota area, in search of River Otters. They discover an array of wildlife, ranging from beaver and porcupine, to Trumpeter Swans and the rare Great Grey Owl!

5.title: Dino Dig: Revisited

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

5.plot: Terri and Todd visit an active dig site north of Baker, Montana. This site is host to several active digs, including Triceratops, Tyrannosaurus Rex and Hadrosaurus sites. They observe excavation teams hard at work and do some exploring for fossils on their own. Todd finds a Prairie Rattlesnake!

6.title: Spelunking Rushmore Cave

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

6.plot: Terri and Todd explore the history and wonders of beautiful Rushmore Cave in the Black Hills of South Dakota. They learn about caves and go spelunking for the first time, which is exciting, yet challenging! They conclude their visit with a ride on the caves newest attraction, the Soaring Eagle Zip line.

7.title: Moose

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

7.plot: Todd and Terri go on a journey to the Rocky Mountains in Colorado in search of Moose! They didn't have to search hard, as it seems the moose in this area were waiting to greet them upon arrival! Come along as we get up close with these wonderful creatures!

8.title: The Sax Zim Bog Birding Festival

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

8.plot: Todd and Terri travel to Northeastern Minnesota to attend the Sax Zim Bog Birding Festival, where they learn about owls and other species that call this unique area 'home' during the winter. They encounter an array of wildlife and observe the rarely-seen Northern Hawk Owl.

9.title: A Day at the Black Hills Wild Horse Sanctuary

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

9.plot: Terri and Todd travel to the Black Hills, home of the Black Hills Wild Horse Sanctuary. They learn about the history and importance of the sanctuary from founder Dayton Hyde. Beautiful horses, history, and scenery unlike any other place on earth, the sanctuary is a magical place!

10.title: Exploring North Platte Nebraska

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

10.plot: Terri and Todd tour the North Platte, Nebraska area, home of the North Platte River. They find Cattle Egrets, Ornate Box Turtles, woodpeckers and more! They visit Dancing Leaf where they get a lesson in history, the Native American culture, and learn all about native plants and how they were used.

11.title: Journey Through Eastern Wyoming

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

11.plot: Terri and Todd travel through Eastern Wyoming to visit Mountain Memories Ranch, which stirs memories from their rural childhoods. They also stop in Bill, Wyoming, get a glimpse of historic Laramie Peak, visit Ayers Natural Bridge, and find some Sagebrush Lizards!

12.title: Making a Comeback

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

12.plot: Terri and Todd visit Lower Brule, SD, where they go on a search for the most endangered land mammal in North America, the Black Footed Ferret. They are accompanied by Lower Brule Wildlife Biologist Shaun Grassel.

13.title: Our Trip to the Southern Black Hills

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

13.plot: Todd and Terri explore the Southern Black Hills Region, where they embark on a journey, via horseback, to the top of the Seven Sisters Mountain Range where they stay in a rustic camp. They also visit the Custer and Hot Springs areas and experience what makes those areas unique.

2.title: Exploring the Grand Tetons of Wyoming

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

2.plot: Terri and Todd trek around the Grand Tetons in Western Wyoming, where they take in beautiful scenery and lots of wildlife, including bison, beaver, and a protective female Common Nighthawk guarding her egg!

3.title: GW Animal Park: Saving the Big Cats

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

3.plot: Terri and Todd visit the GW Animal Park, a sanctuary for big cats. They learn first-hand how an animal rescue works, and witness the important work of organizations such as this. Terri does her part in saving the tigers when she enters a cage to check on 8 day old Siberian Tiger Cubs.

5.title: Discovering the Red Desert

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

5.plot: Terri and Todd explore the Red Desert of Wyoming, an area full of history, unique wildlife and fun! They visit the Boar's Tusk, the neck of an ancient volcano, and play on miles of huge sand dunes. Along their journey, they encounter Wild Horses and rare Desert Elk, which are found no where else in North America.

6.title: Visiting Aransas National Wildlife Refuge

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

6.plot: Terri and Todd explore the Aransas National Wildlife Refuge in Texas, a haven for a wide variety of wildlife, from snakes and turtles to wild boars. Speaking of wild, they even have a close encounter with a Texas Brown Tarantula!

8.title: Journey Through the Mountains of Arkansas and Oklahoma

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

8.plot: Terri and Todd travel through the Ozark Mountains near Fayetteville, Arkansas and the Gloss Mountains near Enid, Oklahoma. On their travels they encounter a Three-Toed Tortoise, a Midland Water Snake, lizards, and much more!

10.title: Destination: Yellowstone!

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

10.plot: Terri and Todd make a trip through Yellowstone National Park, where they take in beautiful waterfalls, breathtaking history and scenery, and encounter an array of wildlife, including elk, bison, bear, Sandhill Cranes and thousands of curiously-clingy salmon flies.

11.title: Pembina County: Hidden Gem of North Dakota

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

11.plot: Terri and Todd head north to explore Pembina County, North Dakota, an area neither of them had visited before, to see what they might be missing. While there, they stop at Icelandic State Park and visit the Pembina Gorge near Walhalla. They also stop in the Black Hills of South Dakota where they find a Mountain Goat in the wild after 5 years of searching.

12.title: Our Visit to the Big Horns of Wyoming

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

12.plot: Terri and Todd travel through the Big Horn Mountains in Wyoming, an area filled with breathtaking beauty and history. They are greeted by some friendly moose and marmots. On the way home, they stop to explore Devil's Tower National Monument, near the South Dakota/Wyoming border, where they are greeted by a town of prairie dogs!

13.title: Gatlinburg, TN: Gateway to Smoky Mountain National Park

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

13.plot: Terri and Todd head to Gatlinburg, TN, home of Smoky Mountain National Park, an area full of beauty, history and wildlife. They teach us about Black Bears and other creatures that call this park home, such as the Red-Cheeked Salamander, a rare species found exclusively in this region!

1.title: Black Hills Wild Horse Sanctuary Revisited

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

1.plot: Terri and Todd revisit the Black Hills Wild Horse Sanctuary where they evaluate changes that one year has made. They talk with founder Dayton O. Hyde about challenges they are faced with and how important it is to respect our land. They also learn about special heritage breeds and rescue horses.

3.title: Florida's West Coast

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

3.plot: Terri and Todd visit the west coast of Florida, a Mecca for bird species. They also observe and learn about manatees and try their luck at deep sea fishing.

4.title: The Everglades: Where Wildlife Abounds

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

4.plot: Terri and Todd explore the Everglades of southern Florida, where wildlife abounds! They even find an endangered American Crocodile!

5.title: Sea Turtles of Mexico

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

5.plot: Terri and Todd visit the Yucatan Peninsula region in southern Mexico to study the behaviors and lives of sea turtles. They work firsthand with a team who is working to protect and preserve the turtles. They witness females laying eggs and watching hatch-lings venture to sea for the first time.

6.title: Cozumel: Island Paradise

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

6.plot: Terri and Todd visit the island paradise where they take in the sites, scenery, history and activities of the island, and a visit to some of the least explored parts of the island. They also have close encounters with dolphins and manatees.

8.title: Montana: A Trek Through the Mountains

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

8.plot: Terri and Todd visit Montana where they journey to the mountains in search of Grizzly Bears. While there, they learn about the importance of the mountain ecosystem and all about the creatures which inhabit the region.

9.title: Exploring Northern Idaho

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

9.plot: Terri and Todd visit northern Idaho where they experience being part of a ranch family. They also explore various wildlife refuges in the area to see what wildlife species they can find.

10.title: The Plains of the Dakotas

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

10.plot: Terri and Todd visit Harding County, South Dakota where they encounter a plethora of magnificent creatures. While there, they visit the Slim Buttes, a unique and fascinating region few have visited.

12.title: Black Hills: Land of the Bison

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

12.plot: Terri and Todd visit the Black Hills Region of South Dakota and the Badlands. While there, they attend the 2013 Buffalo Roundup at Custer State Park, where they learn the history and importance of Bison, and why it's important to keep these magnificent creatures roaming the prairies.

13.title: Glacier Lakes of the Dakotas

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

13.plot: Terri and Todd visit the Sand Lake National Wildlife Refuge in Northeastern South Dakota, which is situated in a major flyway for migrating birds and waterfowl. They witness a mass migration, something everyone should experience!

1.title: Marine Mammals of the West Coast

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

1.plot: Todd and Terri visit Southern California where they explore the Pacific Coast for wildlife. They discovery several species of Dolphins, Sea Lions, Seals, and come upon the first migrating Grey Whales of the season!

2.title: Wildlife of the Florida Keys

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

2.plot: Terri and Todd visit the Florida Keys, an important habitat for several unique and endangered species, including Key Deer, American Crocodiles and Great White Heron. They experience how unique this important group of islands are, and learn that the history behind the geology of the island is fascinating, too!

3.title: Exploring the Sonoran Desert: Yuma AZ

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

3.plot: Todd and Terri travel to Yuma, Arizona to explore the Sonoran Desert which surrounds the city. While there, they explore the area's plants, animals, history and diverse landscapes.

5.title: Bayfield Wi: Gateway to the Apostle Islands

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

5.plot: Terri, Todd and Ashley visit the Bayfield, Wisconsin area, gateway to the Apostle Islands. They visit the Sea Caves, a geological feature in which the area is well-known for. Historic Lighthouses, wildlife, kayaking and spectacular scenery await.

8.title: Baby Animals

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

8.plot: Todd and Terri highlight some encounters they've had with baby animals. They share information about the creatures and discuss animal instincts. Evidence is presented that indicates that animals feel love and pain, like humans do, in this that will melt your heart.

9.title: Things with Wings

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

9.plot: Terri and Todd travel to the East Coast of Florida to go birding. They encounter many species of birds, some of which were unexpected, such as a Black Skimmer! They also discover a Great Blue Heron heronry, or nest site, with some cute Great Blue Heron chicks, and much more!

10.title: Conservation Angels

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

10.plot: Terri and Todd visit the Spirit of The Hills Wildlife Sanctuary in Western South Dakota to experience the works of the sanctuary. They also travel into Mexico with their friends from Pronatura, a conservation working to restore the Colorado River Delta and other wetlands. Each area they visit they realize how important it is for people to work together for the benefit of all the earths resources.

1.title: America's Amazon

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

1.plot: Todd and Terri explore the Mobile-Tensaw Delta in Alabama, and learn the reasons why some people call it "America's Amazon".

2.title: Sea Otters

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

2.plot: Terri and Todd go out looking for Sea Otters. Along the way, they make many other amazing discoveries!

3.title: Wildlife of the Rio Grande Valley

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

3.plot: Terri and Todd make a trek to the Rio Grande Valley in Texas to explore the many diverse habits. While there, they discover an amazing array of wildlife, including the Crested Caracara and some other peculiar birds called Chachalacas.

5.title: Wildlife Rehabilitation and Education

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

5.plot: Terri and Todd travel to Alabama where they visit the Environmental Learning Center. At the Center they introduce us to some of the residents that are enrolled in their rehab program. At the center they see how important is in to use hands-on learning to teach youth about wildlife and nature.

6.title: Wild Parrots of Texas

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

6.plot: Parrots in the wild in the United States? You bet! Today's discovery might come as a surprise to many. they travel to south Texas to experience finding parrots and parakeets in the wild. The northernmost point of their range is closer than they'd expect, and the discovery is a spectacular sight!

7.title: The Living Coast

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

7.plot: The coast of California is teaming with life! Join Todd and Terri on their trek along the coast. Explore tide pools and other habitats, and see some of California's smallest and largest creatures, from tiny snails to huge Elephant Seals!

8.title: Exploring Mobile, Alabama

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

8.plot: Todd and Terri explore the Mobile, Alabama area. They find turtles and tortoises galore and rescue a water moccasin off the road. They also see those pitcher plants.

9.title: Best of Florida

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

9.plot: Florida is a state full of wildlife watching opportunities. Join Terri and Todd as they highlight some of their favorite Florida wildlife encounters! Lots of birds and gators.

10.title: Black Hills Favorite Places

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

10.plot: Terri and Todd visit some of their favorite destinations in the Black Hills of South Dakota. With so many places to explore, they highlight some of our favorite places to visit, and those they encourage everyone to add to their bucket list.

11.title: Pacific Coast of California

episode of.title: Nature Adventures with Terri and Todd (TV Series 2008– )

11.plot: The Pacific Coast in California is a great place for a nature adventure! Join us as they explore the sights and various habitats along the coast, in search of wildlife.
